  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nWhen I have a symlink in minikube from /var/lib/rook --> /mnt/sda1/var/lib/rook, I see the following error when the mon attempts to start:\r\n```\r\nWarning  Failed     11s (x5 over 105s)  kubelet, minikube  Error: failed to start container \"chown-container-data-dir\": \r\nError response from daemon: error while creating mount source path '/var/lib/rook/rook-ceph/log': mkdir /var/lib/rook: file exists\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe workaround is to just use `/mnt/sda1/var/lib/rook` as the `dataDirHostPath`. Not a big deal for development, but I wonder if others might be using symlinks besides this test environment.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nWe should be able to use the `dataDirHostPath` even if it includes a symlink.\r\n@leseb Do we need `chown -H`?\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n- Start minikube\r\n- Create a symlink so the default dataDirHostPath will work:\r\n   - `ln -s /var/lib/rook /mnt/sda1/var/lib/rook`\r\n- Create the cluster\r\n\r\n",
